<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 5000i, 9100i, 9200i, 9400i, 9900i MODELS - Starting 03/01/1999 - REMOVE
        AND INSTALL - CAB BLEND-DOOR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>CAB BLEND-DOOR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcsubproc id="x1602305">
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the key switch and A/C switch are in the OFF position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the passenger seat and Blend-Air unit cover. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16023_17.xml" xrefid="x1602313">BLEND-AIR UNIT COVER, Remove</hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two clips: one securing the cab blend-door assembly to the evaporator (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602337">Figure 28</hotlnk>), and one securing the cab blend-door assembly to the
                    bunk blend-door assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602338">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1602337" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602345.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 28. Clip Securing Cab Blend-Door Assembly to Evaporator</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1602338" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602322.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 29. Clip Securing Cab Blend-Door Assembly to Bunk Blend-Door Assembly (Sleepers) or
                        Dummy Housing (Daycabs)
                    </caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the five nuts that secure the cab blend-door assembly to the bottom of the
                    Blend-Air unit.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>While removing the cab blend-door assembly, in the following step, the linkage to the actuator
                        must be disconnected.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift the cab blend-door assembly straight up and out of the Blend-Air unit (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602339">Figure 30</hotlnk>)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1602339" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602323.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Cab Blend-Door Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x1602306">
            <title>Install</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>While installing the cab blend-door assembly, in the following step, the linkage to the
                        actuator must be reconnected.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the cab blend-door assembly into the Blend-Air unit (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602339">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the five nuts that secure the cab blend-door assembly to the bottom of the case
                    (
                    <hotlnk document="s16023_17.xml" xrefid="f1602302">Figure 10</hotlnk>). Tighten to 13 lbf-in (1.46
                    Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the two clips securing the cab blend-door assembly to the evaporator (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602337">Figure 28</hotlnk>) and the bunk blend-door assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602338">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>In the following step, to verify correct operation at the air duct outlets, the cover must be
                        in place on the Blend-Air unit.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Test operation.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install Blend-Air unit cover and passenger seat. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16023_17.xml" xrefid="x1602314">BLEND AIR UNIT COVER, Install</hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
